definition.value: An member of the class of biphenyls that is 2,2',5,5'-tetrachlorobiphenyl in which the 4 and 4' positions are substituted by methylsulfonyl groups.
A monovalent inorganic anion obtained by deprotonation of periodic acid.
An  aralkylamino compound that is benzylamine substituted by a methoxy group at the para position.
A fatty acid ester that is the carboxylic ester obtained by the formal condensation of a fatty acid with methanol.

A member of the class of tetrahydropterins that is 7,8-dihydropteridin-6(5H)-one substituted by {2-methoxy-4-[(1-methylpiperidin-4-yl)carbamoyl]phenyl}amino, methyl, ethyl, and cyclopentyl groups at positions 2, 5, 7R, and 8, respectively. It is a polo-like kinase 1 (PLK1) inhibitor with antineoplastic activity.
An Fe4S4 iron-sulfur cluster in which each sulfur is attached to three of the iron atoms.
A metal cation comprising samarium in the +3 oxidation state.
An arsenic oxoacid consisting of three hydroxy groups attached to a central arsenic atom.
The complex formed between iron(III) and citrate.
A trichlorobenzene carrying chloro substituents at positions 1, 3 and 5.
A member of the class of thioureas that is thiourea in which a hydrogen of one of the amino groups is replaced by an amino group.

A morpholine-based antiemetic, which is or the prevention of acute and delayed nausea and vomiting associated with initial and repeat courses of highly emetogenic cancer chemotherapy. Aprepitant is a selective high-affinity antagonist of human substance P/neurokinin 1 (NK1) receptors.
The bis(carbamate ester) of 2-phenylpropane-1,3-diol. An anticonvulsant, it is used in the treatment of epilepsy.

A quinazoline that is 7-[(1-methylpiperidin-4-yl)methoxy]quinazoline bearing additional methoxy and 4-bromo-2-fluorophenylamino substituents at positions 6 and 4 respectively. Used for the treatment of symptomatic or progressive medullary thyroid cancer in patients with unresectable locally advanced or metastatic disease.
